title: The renaissance of the Kariri Indigenous people in northeastern Brazil
byline: By Bruno Meyerfeld (Nova Olinda, Crato (Ceará state, Brazil) special correspondent)
subhed: Having inhabited the semi-desert region of Sertao for thousands of years, the population was exterminated by Portuguese colonists. Today, several hundred people openly reclaim their heritage and are proudly celebrating their culture.
